 '$170m' Water Serpents|last=Gerlis|first=Melanie|date=12 Jan 2018|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref> }}\n|-\n! ${{Inflation|US|186|2014|r=0}}\n| $186<br>(\u20ac140)<!-- a round $186 million as used in the news, which would be an exchange rate of $1.3286 per Euro-->\n| ''[[No. 6 (Violet, Green and Red)]]''\n|  <!-- Please don't insert a picture here; artist died less than 70 years ago and work postdates 1923 (see WP:NFC  and specifically WP:NFLISTS) -->\n| {{sort|Rothko, Mark|[[Mark Rothko]]}}\n| 1951\n| {{Dts|2014-08}}\n| 3\n| [[Christian Moueix|Cherise Moueix]]\n| [[Dmitry Rybolovlev]]\n| Private sale via<br>[[Yves Bouvier]]<ref name=ryob>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-27/a-186-million-rothko-pits-russian-tycoon-against-art-merchant | work=Bloomberg | first=Stephanie | last=Baker | title=The Billionaire, the Dealer, and the $186 Million Rothko | date=April 27, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! ${{Inflation|US|180|2015|r=0}}\n| $180<br/>(\u20ac160M)<!--With exchange rate 1\u20ac = $1.125. Forthcoming sale announced 21 September and official permission by Dutch senate October 6 (1\u20ac ~ $1.125 both times); the actual sale must have been later though (rate was ~1.135 the next two weeks, which would be $181.6M) -->\n| ''[[Pendant portraits of Maerten Soolmans and Oopjen Coppit|Pendant portraits of<br>Maerten Soolmans<br>and Oopjen Coppit]]''\n| [[File:Pendant portraits of Maerten Soolmans and Oopjen Coppit.jpeg|95px]]\n| {{sort|Rembrandt|[[Rembrandt]]}}\n| 1634\n| {{Dts|2015-09}}\n| 7\n| [[\u00c9ric de Rothschild]]\n| [[Rijksmuseum]]<br>and [[Louvre]]\n| Private sale<br><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/22/arts/design/rembrandt-portraits-may-come-home-for-record-price-with-government-help.html Rembrandt portraits may come home], The New York Times September 21, 2015</ref>\n|-\n! ${{Inflation|US|179.365|2015|r=1}}\n| $179.4 <!-- $179,365,000 -->\n| ''[[Les Femmes d'Alger (Picasso)#Version \"O\"|Les Femmes d'Alger<br>(\"Version O\")]]''\n| <!-- Please don't insert a picture here; artist died less than 70 years ago and work postdates 1923 (see WP:NFC  and specifically WP:NFLISTS)[[File:Les_femmes_d%E2%80%99Alger,_Picasso,_version_O.jpg|95px]]  -->\n| {{sort|Picasso, Pablo|[[Pablo Picasso]]}}\n| 1955\n| {{Dts|2015-05-11}}\n| 5\n| Private collection\n| [[Hamad bin Jassim bin Jaber Al Thani]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pagesix.com/2015/05/20/buyer-of-record-setting-picasso-painting-revealed/|title=Buyer of record-setting Picasso painting revealed|last=Smith|first=Emily|date=20 May 2015|publisher=Page Six|accessdate=6 February 2016}}</ref>\n| Christie's, New York<ref name=NYTimesPicGiaMay2015>{{cite news|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/05/11/two-art-works-top-100-million-each-at-christies-sale/|title=Picasso and Giacometti Artworks Top $120 Million Each at Christie's Sale|date=11 May 2015|work=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=12 May 2015|first=Scott|last=Reyburn}}</ref>\n|-\n! ${{Inflation|US|170.405|2015|r=1}}\n| $170.4 <!-- $170,405,000 -->\n| ''[[Nu couch\u00e9]]''\n| [[File:Modigliani - Nu couch\u00e9.jpg|95px]]\n| {{sort|Modigliani, Amedeo|[[Amedeo Modigliani]]}}\n| 1917/18\n| {{Dts|2015-11-09}}\n| 9\n| [[Gianni Mattioli|Laura Mattioli Rossi]]\n| [[Liu Yiqian]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/11/arts/international/liu-yiqian-modigliani-nu-couche.html|title=Chinese Taxi Driver Turned Billionaire Bought Modigliani Painting|date=10 November 2015|work=[[New York Times]]|accessdate= 10 November 2015|first=Amy|last=Qin}}</ref>\n| Christie's, New York<ref name=NYTimesMod>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/10/arts/with-170-4-million-sale-at-auction-modigliani-work-joins-rarefied-nine-figure-club.html?hp/|title=With $170.4 Million Sale at Auction, Modigliani Work Joins Rarefied Nine-Figure Club|date=9 November 2015|work=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=9 November 2015|first1=Robin|last1=Pogrebin|first2=Scott|last2=Reyburn}}</ref>\n|-\n! ${{Inflation|US|14