any)]], a French bicycle manufacturer\n* [[Time Inc.]], a New York-based publishing company\n* Time UK, United Kingdom computer retailer [[Granville Technology Group]]\n\n==Computing==\n* [[System time]], a computer's reckoning of real-world time\n* [[Time (metadata)]], a representation term\n* [[time (Unix)]], a shell command on Unix and Unix-like operating systems\n* [[TIME (command)]], a shell command on DOS, OS/2 and Microsoft Windows operating systems\n* [[Time Protocol]], an Internet protocol\n\n==Film and television==\n* [[Time (1999 film)|''Time'' (1999 film)]], in Tamil \n* [[Time (2006 film)|''Time'' (2006 film)]], in South Korean\n* [[Time (2007 film)|''Time'' (2007 film)]], in Malayalam\n* [[Time (British TV programme)|''Time'' (British TV programme)]], a 2006 British documentary television programme about time broadcast on BBC Four\n* [[Time (American TV series)|''Time'' (American TV series)]], actually titled ''Timeless'', is a 2016\u20132018 American television series that aired on NBC\n* [[Time (Doctor Who)|\"Time\" (''Doctor Who'')]], a mini-episode of the television series\n* [[Time (Stargate Universe)|\"Time\" (''Stargate Universe'')]], an episode of ''Stargate Universe''\n* [[Time (The Young Ones)|\"Time\" (''The Young Ones'')]], an episode of ''The Young Ones''\n* [[The Time (TV series)|''The Time'' (TV series)]], a 2018 South Korean television series\n* ''[[Time Gentlemen Please]]'', a British sitcom\n* ''[[Vremya]]'', a Russian TV series whose name translates into English as ''Time''\n\n==Media==\n* [[Time (magazine)|''Time'' (magazine)]], an American weekly news magazine\n* [[Time (xkcd)|\"Time\" (''xkcd'')]], an episode of the webcomic strip\n* ''[[Manifold: Time]]'' (1999), a science fiction novel by Stephen Baxter\n\n==Music==\n===Albums===\n* [[Time (Arashi album)|''Time'' (Arashi album)]], a 2007 release\n* [[Time (Atlantic Starr album)|''Time'' (Atlantic Starr album)]], a 1994 release\n* [[Time (Bunny Rugs album)|''Time'' (Bunny Rugs al